Let’s make some fudge!

Fantasy Fudge is my favorite and so easy to make if you follow the directions exactly!  It’s a family tradition for Christmas.

FANTASY FUDGE
3 cups sugar
3/4 cup butter
2/3 cup evaporated milk
1 (7 oz) jar Kraft Marshmallow crème
1 tsp. vanilla

1.  Stir together the butter, sugar and milk in a saucepan over medium heat until the mixture comes to a full, bubbly boil. 
2.  Continue to boil for exactly 4 minutes and then REMOVE FROM HEAT. 
3.  Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
4.  Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and cool at room temperature and cute into squares.

💚Happy Saturday!  This weekend I plan to give my garden some much needed attention.  I also wanted to try propagating my beautiful pothos plant!  Wish me luck🍀! 

 3 STEPS TO PROPAGATING POTHOS:

1. Take cuttings approximately 4 inches long, making sure that the sections have a few leaves and nodes, which is where the leaves attach to the stem.

2. Place the cut ends in your container making sure the leaves are not submerged but that the nodes and aerial roots are under water. Keep the container in bright, indirect light.  Change the water every few days.

3. When the cuttings start to develop roots and are several inches long, transfer them to a  container with fresh potting soil and place in bright, indirect light.

I’m also using this cute Better Homes and Garden Propagation Station I found  on sale at @walmart

See my bio in stories for the link💚

🌱BENEFITS OF THE POTHOS PLANT:

1.  Low Maintenance houseplant.  The Pothos Plant does well in various conditions–both sun and shade and moist and dry soil.
2.  Easy to Propagate.
3.  Grows without Sunlight
4.  Purifies Indoor Air
5.  Increases Humidity
6.  Looks Great…adds beauty
